  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A multi-phased project to strengthen the design and delivery of ICAG&#x2019;s professional accountancy education, training, and examinations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A project to strengthen the accountancy profession in Ghana through support to the Institute of Chartered Accountants Ghana (ICAG) by the Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales (ICAEW).  The project focuses on increasing ICAG&apos;s relevance and value to members, students, and stakeholders, and facilitating the adoption and implementation of international standards in Ghana by focusing on education, training, and high-quality professional qualification.   Launched under the International Federation of Accountants (IFAC) Professional Accounting Organization (PAO) Capacity Building Program funded by DFID.</narrative>
  </description>
